text: The Kelowna Rockets are a Canadian ice hockey team. They began playing in 1991. The team currently plays in the Western Hockey League. They play their home games in Kelowna, British Columbia at the Prospera Place. The team originally played in Tacoma, Washington as the Tacoma Rockets from 1991 to 1995 until relocating to Kelowna. They have won 3 Ed Chynoweth Cups and 1 Memorial Cup. ==Other websites== *Official website Category:Canadian Hockey League teams Category:Western Hockey League Category:Ice hockey teams in British Columbia Category:Tacoma, Washington Category:1991 establishments in Canada
